[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "01 Open Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "crush-the-slav-with-the-boor-attack/course/11611, variation/655706"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 6. e4 dxe4 {The most forcing 
variation which we shall call the Open Variation.} 7. d5 Ne5 8. fxe4 e6 {By no means 
the only move, but the most natural.} 9. Nf3 {Develop with Attack!} Nxf3+ 10. Qxf3 
exd5 11. e5 Ne4 12. Bb5+ Bd7 13. Rf1 {A crucial improvement over 0-0 which would 
allow black to escape with Qb6+.} f6 14. exf6 Nxf6 15. Qe2+ $1 {Setting a deadly 
trap.} Be7 16. Rxf6 $3 {A hammer blow that releases the black king from this plane of 
existence.} gxf6 17. Qh5+ Kf8 18. Bh6+ Kg8 19. Qxd5+ Be6 20. Qxe6# *

