[SourceTitle "01 Open Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "crush-the-slav-with-the-boor-attack/course/11611, variation/655716"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 6. e4 dxe4 7. d5 Ne5 8. fxe4 Bg4 
9. Qd4 {If black moves the knight from the center then e5 is just winning.} Nfd7 
{This move will force black to put his bishop offside. If black ever plays Ng6 then 
g4 may trap the bishop.} 10. h3 $1 Bh5 {Now black has a real problem finishing 
development.} 11. Bf4 Qc7 $2 {The wretched pawn to f6 was forced.} 12. Bb5 $14 {[%cal 
Bf4e5,Bb5e8][%csl Be5,Bd7] Black has a terrible position.} *

