1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 6. e4 dxe4 7. d5 exf3 $2 {This 
move is often played in blitz by surprised opponent's looking to refute the Boor 
Attack at first guess. The knight sacrifice does not have any real validity if we 
take care.} 8. dxc6 f2+ 9. Kxf2 Qb6+ 10. Ke1 $1 {There is no need to allow the 
complications of Be3 when black can try Ng4+ or Qxb2.} bxc6 11. Nf3 {True white can 
not castle, but Qb3 offering trades is in the works. White is winning.} *

