[SourceTitle "01 Open Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "crush-the-slav-with-the-boor-attack/course/11611, variation/673814"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 6. e4 e5 {A principal reaction 
however white's mobile pawns can gain the initiative over the black knights.} 7. dxe5 
Nxe5 8. f4 {[%csl Bd5] Essentially a double attack against d5 and e5 however we 
should take care when it comes to capturing the d5 pawn lest black gain 
counter-play.} Bg4 {This developing move is given as best by engines. The trouble 
with this move though is that it also encourages white to develop the forces.} 9. Be2 
Bxe2 10. Qxe2 {[%cal Be2e8] A useful line of attack for white. I have also analyzed 
Ngxe2 and it is leads to some advantage.} Nc6 11. exd5+ Ne7 12. Nf3 {White returns 
the pawn for development.} Nxd5 13. Nxd5 Qxd5 14. O-O {Black has trouble completing 
development. White will simply connect the rooks and lay siege to the king and 
seventh rank.} *

