[White "7...Ng8!?"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "02 Closed Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "crush-the-slav-with-the-boor-attack/course/11611, variation/655842"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 6. e4 e6 7. e5 Ng8 {Rarely played 
but superior to Nd7 as the knight has greater potential on f5.} 8. Be3 Nge7 9. Bd3 
{My improvement for white. We will capture the knight at f5 and reserve f4 for our 
knight where it will exert pressure on d5 and the kingside. This is an unusual hybrid 
French structure where white has good chances to outplay the opponent with greater 
development and space.} Qb6 {More challenging than Nf5.} 10. Qd2 Bd7 11. Nge2 g6 12. 
O-O Bg7 13. Na4 {In French structures Na4 is a common response to Qb6.} Qa5 14. Qxa5 
Nxa5 15. Nc5 Nc4 16. Bc1 {[%cal Bb2b3][%csl Bb3] White has a slight positional pull.} 
*

[Event "Crush the Slav with the Boor Attack"]
[Site "Closed Variation"]
