8. Nge2 Bd6 9. e4 {We should always keep this pawn break at the center of our 
attention.} Bb4 10. O-O O-O 11. Kh1 dxe4 12. fxe4 Nxe4 13. Bd3 Nf6 14. Rxf6 {this 
leads to a probable draw, there is nothing wrong with continuing on with gambit style 
with normal moves such as 14.a3 or 14.Bg5.} gxf6 15. Bxh7+ Kxh7 16. Qd3+ {[%cal 
Bd3h3][%csl Bg3,Bh3] With at least a forced draw.} *

