1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. f3 Qa5 {Black can prevent the pawn to e4 
break with this move but in the longterm the queen is misplaced in comparison to the 
normal exchange slav.} 6. Bg5 Nc6 7. a3 e6 8. e3 Be7 9. Bd3 O-O 10. Ne2 {improving 
over Boor - Zatonskih 2004. White has a fleixble position and will eventually exploit 
the Queen at a5 with pawn to b4.} *

