1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. f3 e6 6. e4 dxe4 7. fxe4 Bb4 8. Bg5 
{More accurate than 8...Bxc3 as now 9.e5 Nd5 would overpower c3 knight under 
favorable circumstances.} Qa5 9. Bxf6 Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 Qxc3+ {Black can attempt to win 
a pawn at their peril.} 11. Kf2 {[%cal Bc1c8][%csl Bc8]} Qb2+ $1 12. Be2 gxf6 13. Nf3 
{Following the game Lawson - Jameson England 2018. I was pleased to discover that 
this gambit position is very difficult for black. White plans to play Qd3 and trap 
the black queen. The black king will suffer on the dark squares in the long run.} Nc6 
14. Qd3 Nb4 $2 15. Qe3 Nc2 16. Qd2 {And black loses the knight.} *

