1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nc6 5. e4 dxe4 6. d5 Nb8 {Stronger than Ne5. A 
common thread that we have seen in many variation is the knight retreating to home 
base offers greater resistance.} 7. Nxe4 {By far the easiest move to play but I will 
give a sharp gambit like alternative in the next chapter.} Nf6 8. Nxf6+ exf6 9. Bb5+ 
Bd7 10. Qe2+ Qe7 11. Be3 {We are following Andreikin - Goganov World Cup 2017. Black 
can equalize here with exact play but white should have reasonable chances to outplay 
the opponent in the endgame with the presence of a passed pawn.} *

