1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nc6 5. e4 e5 6. dxe5 {6.Bb5 pin is also 
interesting, but I feel this capture should be the focus of exploration in this fresh 
position.} d4 {Black is using our own weapons against us ! If black maintains the 
copy cat game with 6...dxe4 then 7.Qxd8 breaks the mirror with a slightly better 
ending.} 7. Nd5 {Black is down a pawn but can try to formulate a gambit style 
offensive.} Nge7 {A strong move and improvement over the scant few games that have 
been played.} 8. Bg5 $1 Qa5+ 9. Bd2 Qd8 {Other possibilities exist but I feel this is 
the best path for attacking the king.} 10. Nxe7 Bxe7 11. f4 {White will meke good use 
of this pawn roller in the middlegame.} O-O 12. Bd3 {Stopping the advance of the 
d-pawn.} Qb6 13. Nf3 {White returns the pawn in order to smoothly complete 
development.} Qxb2 14. O-O {The five vs three pawn majority on the kingside gurantees 
attacking play for white on that sector.} *

