1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 e5 {The Winawer Counter Gambit.} 5. dxe5 d4 6. 
Nb1 {6.Ne4 is slightly more common but I found an interesting plan in this line.} 
Qa5+ 7. Bd2 $1 Qxe5 {7...Qb6 would simply be met with 8.Qb3 and white is a solid pawn 
up.} 8. Nf3 {Suddenly the black queen and the pawn at d4 are running into some 
difficulties.} Qf6 {Instead 8..Qd5 would run into 9.Bc3! winning a clean extra pawn 
while 8...Qd6 is met by 9.Na3 with further attack on the black queen.} 9. Bg5 Qf5 10. 
Qxd4 Nc6 11. Qa4 {Black should not have enough play to justify the sacrificed pawn.} 
*

