1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 e6 {With this humble move black agrees to close 
in the light square bishop and sumbit to a passive defense. I do not see any reason 
to not play along the lines lines of the 'normal' exchange variation with 5.Bf4 and 
hold a pleasant advantage.} 5. Bf4 {If you really want to keep the opening 
independent then I would encourage you to consider 5.f3 followed by 6.e4.} Nf6 6. e3 
Nc6 7. Bd3 Bd6 {Of course black can play 7...Be7 but then I like 8.h3 followed by 
natural development.} 8. Bxd6 Qxd6 {White has won some nice games in this reverse 
stonewall middlegame. I encourage you to look up the games in the databases and check 
for yourself.} 9. f4 $14 *

