1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nc6 5. e4 e6 {Black has a useful resource if he 
is a French player. The game can now transpose to the Advance French with 6.e5. This 
is beyond the scope of this training file but I would advise you to study the line 1. 
e4 e6 2.d4 d5 3.e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5.Nf3 Qb6 and then focus on lines where black plays 
cxd4. As this may not be to everyone's taste I will suggest a method of play more 
along the lines of the Exchange French where the play is quite natural and only 
requires basic understanding of the principals of development.} 6. exd5 exd5 7. Nf3 
Nf6 8. Bg5 {This move I feel with set the most problems for black.} Be7 9. Be2 Bg4 
10. O-O O-O 11. h3 Bf5 12. Bd3 {The position is equal but still contains plenty of 
life.} *

